The paper focuses on the safety and reliability of autonomous driving systems, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and cybersecurity (cs.CR) categories. The development of Kayotee, a fault injection-based tool, involves the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and system engineering (cs.SY) techniques. The study also considers the vehicle dynamics and traffic resilience, which are relevant to the robotics (cs.RO) category.
